We love ordering delivery & pick up from this place. Highlights include the steak, crab puttanesca, calamari, and ceviche. Tiramisu is also one of the best I’ve had! The gentleman that works here/runs the place is incredibly friendly, even during such hard times. Can’t wait for things to open back up again so we can eat indoors and visit this place for live music too.

This place is a hidden gem. For starters, the place is just beautiful. I had the privilege to meet Francisco (hope I got it right) which is the motivational force behind this review. The out of this world courtesy, kindness, professionalism and customer service he displayed definitely made a lasting impact. I'm definitely looking forward to revisiting Concrete post-pandemic and I recommend you do too. Francisco is great and his presence makes the place very welcoming. Thank you!

Update dropping to 1 star - we went on Dec 13th '20, last day for indoor dinning to support a local restaurant. Bad choice, they deserve to close. Owner/Mgr Francisco was rude AF to my wife when at leaving and paying the bill she mentioned that our app came out cold...we didn't even send it back cause felt bad for businesses during these lockdowns. We've either dinned in or ordered out from here 20 or so times, but will never do so again. The hostess/bartender/waitress wearing multiple hats was the only redeeming quality about the joint. ............. Update dropping from 5 to 3: I have been for brunch and thoroughly enjoyed it, however I did a take order for dinner recently and it left a lot to be desired. We ordered the burger and chicken sandwich and both were just Okay - mediocre at best. Both Items seem like they come prepackaged and are just heated up. The chicken is pre-breaded and then fried and the burger patty comes already made and then just put it on the grill like a fast food place. The fries, both potato and sweet potato, were good, but I won't be ordering either of these items again. The pasta is good from experience - so go there for that, but SkyTown, across the street has Far Better sandwiches.

With a discreet entrance tucked away in the Bushwick triangle of Broadway, Lewis, and Stockton streets it would be an easy place to miss. Often times though, I find that those are the places that make the best dining experiences. This is no exception, with its ample menu full of American-style to Italian-style cuisine and everything in between, you too will have fun trying to pair the best meal with the best extravagant cocktail. The spot also boasted live music pre-Covid era and as she, the owner, explained to me upon exiting, if you like music with reggae ska vibes then check out #eyespynowifi a local Brooklyn band that performed there regularly. Now for me, there's nothing better than having a soundtrack with your eats!
Awesome staff I definitely will go back each time I am in NY

Very nice brunch and lunch spot. Genuinely nice place to grab food. Coffee, tea, and food is good and the location is clean and welcoming. Choose this spot if you want a nice casual brunch experience, it'll be worth your time.
The food and service were above our expectations. We surely enjoyed the environment of this spot. First-rate place to take the family out for lunch.

Really awesome Italian place that serves diverse food (but the pasta is also amazing). Friendly service, great food, and as I was typing this the bartender gave us a sample of the best tiramisu I’ve had in years. Had the meatballs, bruschetta and mussels.
Top quality meals made with passion. I don't know how they manage to keep the prices as low as they do for the standard of food and service.

I've been here a few times for dinner and now once for brunch. The staff is always super friendly and helpful. It's very cute and homey inside, and usually isn't too crowded. The food is amazing, between myself and the people I've brought we have tried the pasta, burgers, chicken sandwich and french toast and loved it all. Drinks (coffee + alcohol) are good too and reasonably priced for the area. Definitely a go-to place now!

My son took us here for an early Sunday night dinner. He said, Mom the food is so good here! I’ll be the judge of that. He was right!!! We were met by friendly and attentive staff. Before you sit watch the cooks in the kitchen cook to go orders and In House orders. It’s amazing how fast their able to cook great food at such a fast pace. My son and husband ordered burgers and I ordered the chicken sandwich. My sandwich was full of flavor. Topped with a slaw, onions, tomatoes, and honey mustard. My side order of French fries were  amazing. (I consider myself a French Fry connoisseur.) Portions are a nice size. I paired my sandwich with a their Etna bianco. Great food and service!!!

Nice cozy spot, good vibe and very delicious food.  I had the shrimp burger with avocado and a light fresh spring salad and a side of chic pea fritter, this was an amazing meal, layered with flavor. And the prices are very reasonable, can't wait to go back.for breakfast, and brunch.

So glad we came here! The happy hour menu was great. We got the burger and the pomodoro, tiramisu and several of the cocktails. The price is right, and the hostess/waitress (Candice) was an absolute gem and took the experience from great to sensational.

Great experience at Concrete! Very cool and cozy place, nice and fine taste for details. Felt in love with the artsworks. Food and drinks were great and very high quality. Atmosphere was perfect, as well as for the music. Francesco, the owner, took care of us, we had a really faboulos dinner: caponata+panelle, arancino, polpette, fried calamari, puorcu, sausage, burgers, sweet potatoes, the amazing Tiramisù! I totally felt home! Highly recommended 👍🏽

The vibe in concrete is wonderful: a dark and moody red flooded the area creating an intimate and warm dining atmosphere. Candice, the owner, is a total sweetheart and goes out of her way to make sure everything is going smoothly for her guests! The Italian dishes were excellent; you can't go wrong with the caponata, pasta dishes, or fish. Concrete has one area of weakness: it would be better off sticking to its strengths and straying away from the American menu additions, like the burgers and fries.

Concrete was very inviting. I brought 5 of my friends here and we had a nice intimate dinner with lots of Wine. There was only one option for a red wine but it was very good! We had calamari and pasta and dessert. It was delicious! I will definitely come back!!
awesome brunch. great folks! the pancakes are V BIG!

Really beautiful space you wouldn’t expect just off of the chaotic hustle n bustle that is the Myrtle Broadway thoroughfare.  The space is enormous! 20 foot high ceilings, a back stage for performances, minimally but sophisticatedly designed.  The food and service can either be great, or it can be hit or miss, or it can just be closed.  I’ve come here a few times where they were closed by 8pm because they sold out of food.  I’ve come here before for a delicious pasta and sandwich and cocktail.  I’ve also come here when the waitress forgot our drink order completely, then served us kinda cold burgers, then got the side orders wrong, and that was a $70 bill.  So, it’s ambitious for Brooklyn- to bring well priced, well designed elegant dining to the neighborhood.  4 stars for effort. Just wish it could be run more consistent, and less Brooklyn lackadaisical!

Great place for happy hour; burger, fries and a beer for $14, doesn't get better than that. While I would consider this place "Sicilian" (although they do serve pasta) the atmosphere was nice and our server welcoming. Tiramisu was good too.

New HOT italian restaurant in Bedstuy Brooklyn. Concrete is a modern concept chill and sophisticated sicilian based eatery, where the neat and stony industrial decor roughly slaps an opulent menu that offers lighter versions of a very rich typical Sicilian cuisine. It’s a place where details have benn pulled to the maximum but it still makes you feel like you are lounging in your living room. Just the food by itself is worth at least 2 tries, so you make sure you try more items!! My new fav spot just a few blocks from my living room 😱😱😱😱😱😱😍😍 Love at first bite
New on the block, really interesting mix of traditionl italian and hipster specials.  Worth a visit.

OMG! So good! Very attentive and sweet staff. Real authentic Sicilian food. So delicious, fresh ingredients, great ambiance. The space is open and welcoming, the people are dope. The food was just perfection. It felt like they just took a few chapters out of "Eat, Pray, Love" (book/movie) and dropped it in BK. The food was just made with love, great! Yummmmz.
